http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Establishments-fined/article13979290.ece

Some hospitals, clinics as well as restaurants in Koramangala were fined heavily by the Bruhut Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike for not disposing hazardous waste in the manner prescribed, as well as not segregating waste. “The total collections came upto Rs. 2, 75,000. These places generate bulk waste and we have certain agencies that are supposed to collect this waste after this is properly segregated. However, these establishments were not doing it. The medical waste was also not being disposed in the proper manner,” said a BBMP spokesperson.These establishments included posh restaurants, beauty parlours, coffee shops and ice-cream parlours.